contents.title: Victrola - Hollow Nation (1982, Bologna Sessions)
contents.description_html: Italian band Victrola's song 'Hollow Nation', from 1982, this version is taken from their Bologna Sessions, as stated by official members taken from the official victrola page, although the page itself is outdated so i can't link it due to safety reasons... get a self-made bootleg for completionists and curious listeners here!

contents.title: JOEY ANDERSON - Attitude (LATENCY 02)
contents.description_html: JOEY ANDERSON - From One Mind to The Other On Press Play, a splintered male vocal plays out over disdainful kicks. Devoid of a bassline, the framework hangs in mid-air. Fluttering synths and cascading keys combine to tough but eerily soothing effect.

contents.title: MADTEO - Irreconcilable Indifferences (LATENCY 05)
contents.description_html: MADTEO - Raveyard Shifts Playing hide-and-seek with over-textured layers that by turns develop paradoxical feelings of warmth and insecurity, melodically blowing hot and cold, the NYC-based producer steers his boat on sight. Every sample resonates in and out of its little loop box, both focused on and digressed from, unfolding sub-structures inside the bigger picture in a permanent dawn of subjugation.
